claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table presenting percentages of local (pain, redness, swelling, bruising) and systemic (headache, fatigue, muscle pain, nausea, joint pain, chills, fever) adverse events by severity (any, moderate, severe) for Flublok (N=2272) versus placebo (N=2231). The table only shows safety and tolerability data (adverse event rates) for Flublok versus placebo and contains no information on antigenic match or strain selection, so it does not support the claim. Note: None
